definition.value: A member of the class of imidazolines that is 4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazole which is substituted by a 1H-indole-3-carbonyl group at position 2 and a 6-bromo-1H-indol-3-yl group at position 4S. It is a bisindole alkaloid isolated from the marine sponge, Spongosorites sp.

An aromatic ketone that is imidazole which is substituted by a 1H-indole-3-carbonyl group and a 6-bromo-1H-indol-3-yl group at  positions 2 and 4, respectively. Isolated from the Mediterranean shallow-water sponge, Topsentia genetrix. It is a potent inhibitor of MRSA pyruvate kinase and exhibits antibacterial properties.

An aromatic ketone that is imidazole that is substituted at positions 2 and 5 by (6-hydroxy-1H-indol-3-yl)carbonyl and 6-bromo-1H-indol-3-yl groups respectively. Isolated from Mediterranean shallow-water sponges Topsentia genetrix, and from Caribbean deep-sea sponges of the Halichondriidae family, it has antitumour and antiviral properties. Toxic to fish.

An N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl group obtained formally by removal of the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of D-mannosylated alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc. In the structure shown, one of the R atoms represents a D-mannopyranosyl group; all remaining R atoms = H.
A phosphoethanolamine-glycosyl-phosphatidylinositol derivative where R1 can be an alkyl or an acyl group, R2 and R3 are both acyl groups of undefined composition.
A phosphoethanolamine-glycosyl-phosphatidylinositol derivative where R1 can be an alkyl or an acyl group, R2 and R3 are both acyl groups of undefined composition.
A phosphoethanolamine-glycosyl-phosphatidylinositol derivative where R1 can be an alkyl or an acyl group, R2 and R3 are both acyl groups of undefined composition.

A member of the class of (trifluoromethyl)benzenes that is 4-amino-2-(trifluoromethyl)benzonitrile in which one of the amino hydrogens is substituted by a 3-[(4-fluorophenyl)sulfonyl]-2-hydroxy-2-methylpropanoyl group.
A N-[4-cyano-3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl]-3-[(4-fluorophenyl)sulfonyl]-2-hydroxy-2-methylpropanamide that is the (S)-enantiomer of bicalutamide.
A flavonoid oxoanion resulting from the deprotonation of the hydroxy group of 5-hydroxy-3,3',4',7-tetramethoxyflavone. The major species at pH 7.3.
Any EC 1.4.3.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor CH-NH2 group, oxygen as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of L-amino-acid oxidase (EC 1.4.3.2).
